1 The employing unit shall pay the employer premiums for retirees who enroll
2 under this subdivision."
3 SECTION 2.(f) The State Treasurer shall seek a private letter ruling from the Internal
4 Revenue Service to determine if any provisions of this section jeopardize the status of the
5 Teachers' and State Employees' Retirement System.
6 SECTION 2.(g) If the Internal Revenue Service determines that any provision of
7 this section jeopardizes the status of the Teachers' and State Employees' Retirement System of
8 North Carolina under the Internal Revenue Code, then this section is repealed on the last day of
9 the month following the month of receipt of that determination by the State Treasurer. Upon
10 receipt of that determination, the State Treasurer shall notify the Revisor of Statutes of the
11 determination and the date of receipt. Within three business days of receipt of the determination,
12 the State Treasurer shall notify all local school administrative units of the repeal of this section
13 and shall publicly notice the receipt of this information on the Department of State Treasurer's
14 website. Within three business days of receipt of the notice from the State Treasurer, a local
15 school administrative unit shall notify all high-need retired teachers employed by its local board
16 of education of the repeal of this section.
17 SECTION 2.(h) Notwithstanding any other provision of law to the contrary, in order
18 to pay costs associated with the administration of the provisions of this section, the Retirement
19 Systems Division of the Department of State Treasurer may increase receipts from the retirement
20 assets of the Teachers' and State Employees' Retirement System or pay costs associated with the
21 administration directly from the retirement assets.
22 SECTION 2.(i) Any beneficiary that is employed by a local board of education as a
23 high-need retired teacher, as defined in G.S. 115C-302.4(a), shall not be eligible to elect into a
24 position that would lead the beneficiary to be eligible to accrue any additional benefits under
25 G.S. 135-3(a)(8). Any failure of a local board of education or a beneficiary to comply with the
26 foregoing shall be corrected by the Executive Director of the Retirement System as may be
27 appropriate under State and federal law. Any costs of the correction, as determined by the
28 Executive Director of the Retirement System, shall be the sole responsibility of the local board
29 of education and shall be transferred to the Pension Accumulation Fund under G.S. 135-8 under
30 rules adopted by the Board of Trustees.
31 SECTION 2.(j) Effective July 1, 2025, there is appropriated from the General Fund
32 to the Department of State Treasurer the sum of one hundred thousand dollars ($100,000) in
33 nonrecurring funds for the 2025-2026 fiscal year to be used to obtain the private letter ruling
34 under subsection (f) of this section.
35 SECTION 2.(k) Effective July 1, 2025, there is appropriated from the General Fund
36 to the Department of State Treasurer the sum of ten million dollars ($10,000,000) in recurring
37 funds for each year of the 2025-2027 fiscal biennium to be used to address the increased cost to
38 the Teachers' and State Employees' Retirement System as a result of the implementation of this
39 section.
40 SECTION 3. This act is effective when it becomes law. G.S. 115C-302.4, as
41 reenacted by this act, applies beginning with the 2025-2026 school year, and this act shall not
42 expire except by subsequent enactment of the General Assembly.
